28/12/2008
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police said on Saturday (December 27th) they arrested two Bosnian Muslims suspected of torturing and killing Serb civilians and prisoners of war during the 1992-1995 conflict. Sulejman Berbic and Camil Bilic were detained on Friday in the northern village of Vecici, near the town of Kotor Varos. The former members of the Bosnian army are suspected of torturing Serb civilians and soldiers, Judge Zelimir Lepir said. They are also suspected in connection with the deaths of two Serb prisoners of war. The alleged war crimes were committed in Vecici between July and October 1992. (AFP, Glas Srpske, RTRS - 27/12/08)
